cd stock_db_builder/

 The overall idea is to create master-JSON from yahoo.
 Then add incrementally into the master-JSON - such as
 themes, index etc. for each company.


1. (Optional)
    Run 'python test_nse.py'
    Run 'python build_database.py'

    This will create output/nse_companies.json

2. Create master database

    python build_database.py

    This will create output/stocks_master.json
    It currently contains approx 2384 companies.

3. Create template knowledge/themes.json

    python build_themes.py

    This will take the master-database from #2 
    above - and add themes.

4. No need to create JSON inside knowledge/ - the script
   will download from NSE etc.

   python build_indices.py

   This will modify master-JSON with indices for each company.









